Package: lwanga
Architecture: amd64 arm64
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}, llvm-18, binutils, build-essential
Description: Security-focused systems programming language
 Lwanga is a low-level systems programming language designed for
 security research, penetration testing, and shellcode development.
 .
 Features:
  - Direct syscall support
  - Inline assembly with Intel and AT&T syntax
  - Position-independent code generation
  - Encrypted string literals
  - Minimal runtime overhead
  - Native code compilation via LLVM
 .
 This package includes:
  - lwangac: The Lwanga compiler
  - lwangafmt: Code formatter with logo headers
  - lwangacat: Syntax highlighter for terminal
  - Standard library and examples
